1
00:00:00,208 --> 00:00:07,958
It was designated as a solitary cell without
a ventilation opening toward the garage

2
00:00:08,416 --> 00:00:11,208
It was a small room where they
placed those sentenced to death

3
00:00:11,875 --> 00:00:14,166
So they had no chance to escape

4
00:00:14,625 --> 00:00:20,250
It was far from the investigation room–
We never knew who entered or left it

5
00:00:22,583 --> 00:00:26,875
In the other solitary cells, we could feel
when prisoners were brought in or taken out

6
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:31,375
Here, we never knew what was happening outside

7
00:00:31,958 --> 00:00:34,583
Witness: We could only communicate a little
Interviewer: How many days did you stay here?

8
00:00:34,625 --> 00:00:36,166
I stayed here for 15 days

9
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:40,458
At first, they left me alone for about 10 days

10
00:00:41,083 --> 00:00:44,333
Then they brought the young man, Faisal Saad Rajoub

11
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:50,666
We stayed five or six days together, and a little
further from our cell was another with two women

12
00:00:51,375 --> 00:00:52,375
They brought in...

13
00:00:54,541 --> 00:01:00,875
A well-known prisoner, so they changed everyone’s places

14
00:01:02,166 --> 00:01:03,833
The young man and I

15
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:08,875
Were placed in the group cell, and
the women were moved to solitary cells

16
00:01:08,916 --> 00:01:11,541
They took one woman, and the
other stayed two days before leaving

17
00:01:12,458 --> 00:01:16,750
After several days, they brought
the male prisoner and placed him here

18
00:01:17,125 --> 00:01:20,875
I communicated with him through
the bathroom; that’s how we talked

19
00:01:21,750 --> 00:01:24,541
He told me his name was Ahmad al-Hassan al-Ibrahim

20
00:01:25,250 --> 00:01:28,208
He was imprisoned for the second
time because of his brother Musleh

21
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:31,250
Who had been sentenced to
death and was in the first solitary cell

22
00:01:31,708 --> 00:01:35,333
He was chained to prevent him from escaping
